---
description: Require release builds to package and upload artifacts to GitHub Releases
alwaysApply: true
---

# Media-Magic Release Upload Rule

- Every completed `release` build must produce a zipped `.app` artifact.
- Every completed `release` build must upload that artifact to a GitHub Release
  tagged with the build ID (`<VERSION>+<BUILD_NUMBER>`).
- If upload preconditions are missing (e.g., unauthenticated `gh`), fail the
  release build rather than silently skipping upload.
- Use `gh release create` when release tag is missing; otherwise use
  `gh release upload --clobber` to update the artifact.
- Keep artifact naming deterministic:
  - `MediaMagic-<VERSION>+<BUILD_NUMBER>-macOS.zip`
